s of those using these technologies. Gerrits contends that to understand the use of reproductive technologies in practice and the complexity of processes of medicalization, we need to go beyond ‘easy assumptions’ about the hegemony of biomedicine and the expected impact of patient-centredness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aFertilization in vitro. 7aMEDICAL / Reproductive Medicine & Technology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311099822140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781785332272?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781785332272423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781785332272/original  a978-3-11-099822-1  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK